actually is indeed the case.

00:00:31.054 --> 00:00:33.511
When x is greater than three,

00:00:33.511 --> 00:00:35.914
we see that our function
is indeed decreasing.

00:00:35.914 --> 00:00:38.497
As x increases, the y value,

00:00:39.440 --> 00:00:42.429
the value of our function, decreases.

00:00:42.429 --> 00:00:44.092
So, a calculus-based justification,

00:00:44.092 --> 00:00:45.985
without even looking at the choices,

00:00:45.985 --> 00:00:47.538
well, I could look at the derivative.

00:00:47.538 --> 00:00:49.288
